==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: loudspeaker
<hw>loud"speak*er</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A device which converts
electrical signals into sounds loud enough to be heard at a distance,
usually outdoors; it is used to amplify or transmit over a distance
speech from a person, who is typically speaking into a microphone.
Sometimes it is used to play recorded speech or music.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> speaker, speaker unit, loudspeaker system, speaker
system.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Loud-voiced</ent>⟦br⟧
